						               													<description>Players are apprentice wizards working in a magical bakery. They use magic spells and cooperation from other players to bake all of the ordered pastries.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn, a player either looks at a baked good card or goes home early (placing one money in the center as a tip.) If they look at the baked good card, they can add it to the stack of orders to be fulfilled, or discard it and hide one of the eight notes with the magic spells on them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When only one player remains, they attempt to bake all of the bread. Each bread card has a die combination that needs to be made. They only get a single roll, but the remaining spell cards  will help them reroll or manipulate the dice, and they can bribe other players to reroll the dice for them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a player succeeds, they earn the tip pool and the value of all of the items they baked. If they fail, they get nothing; the second time they fail, they are fired (eliminated from the game.)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal is to be the first to get to a set goal of money, or the last person still employed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
